snippet.textDisplay:
It's because the league is scripted entertainment. The Chiefs were supposed to win and when the score got out of hand and the Texans went up 24-0 what happened was the 'moles' on the Texans began playing to lose. A 'mole' is a player recruited by the league while still in college. They are promised a lucrative NFL career as long as they follow the league's script and play to lose when required. Moles are placed on every NFL roster so the league can control the scripts. The highest percentage of Moles are placed in the other three teams in the AFC East to ensure that the Patriots always have an easy path to the playoffs. This is why the other three teams (Dolphins, Bills and Jets) have been so consistently inept during the entire Patriot dynasty.


Refs are also part of the script and will favor whichever team is supposed to win. This is the big secret of pro football: Allowing one of the teams to commit offensive and defensive holding will almost guarantee they will win the game. And since some sort of hold occurs on almost every play of the game, all the zebras have to do is selectively call the holds in a way that favors one of the teams.


Moles and Refs are used to fulfill the script - sometimes a certain team is supposed to win and other times the game is just supposed to be close and thrilling. In that case the moles placed on both teams will help whichever team is losing to get back into the game.


Studying the Jets/Colts Super Bowl is a good way to overcome the initial doubt that the NFL is capable of scripting a game. Anyone who examines all the facts realizes that this game was definitely rigged to protect the television revenue - which required an AFC team to win a Super Bowl to seal the contract with the networks.


NFL makes no claim that the games are NOT scripted and no laws are broken if they pre-designate the winner of a contest. It's just like the 'don't ask don't tell' concept of pro-wrestling. The fans of wrestling may or may not be aware that they are watching scripted entertainment. As long as the show is produced it really doesn't matter. The more intelligent fans are bound to deduce the truth and the goofy fans might never figure it out.


The simple truth is that fans are incredibly naive to believe that any business capable of producing billions in revenue is being left to random chance. Authentic sports competition just isn't as superficially entertaining as exhibition-sporting entertainment. You cannot expand and increase your mass audience and sustain your vast profits without re-inventing the games to provide the maximum, fast-paced and star-driven spectacle that can only be ensured with scripted entertainment. Fans are like gullible little kids who don't understand the motives of capitalism and multi-millionaires and billionaires. These hardened capitalists care absolutely nothing for the competitive aspect when billions of dollars are involved.
